Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    echo "Updating apt and installing Python/pip..."
    apt-get update -y
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    echo "Creating required directory structure..."
    mkdir -p /home/user/firewall_configs

    echo "Writing iptables_prometheus.rules..."
    cat > /home/user/firewall_configs/iptables_prometheus.rules <<'RULES'
*filter
:INPUT DROP [0:0]
:FORWARD DROP [0:0]
:OUTPUT ACCEPT [0:0]
-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22   -j ACCEPT
-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 9090 -j ACCEPT
-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 3000 -j ACCEPT
-A INPUT -p tcp --dport 9100 -j ACCEPT
COMMIT
RULES

    echo "Writing report_firewall.log..."
    cat > /home/user/report_firewall.log <<'REPORT'
22,ALLOWED
9090,ALLOWED
3000,ALLOWED
9100,ALLOWED
3306,DENIED
REPORT

    echo "Setting permissions..."
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user/firewall_configs
    chmod 644 /home/user/firewall_configs/iptables_prometheus.rules
    chmod 644 /home/user/report_firewall.log

%labels
    Author firewall-observability-setup
    Description "Container prepared for firewall configuration exercise with pytest pre-installed."

%help
This Apptainer image sets up the initial state for the “Prometheus / Grafana / node-exporter firewall” exercise.
It provides:
  • /home/user/firewall_configs/iptables_prometheus.rules
  • /home/user/report_firewall.log
  • pytest (installed via pip)

No iptables rules are applied—only staged for later use by privileged operators.